{
  "texts": [
    "In the quantum regime, the HQ effective temperature is 10% to 20% higher than the medium temperature.",
    "This is due to the UV regularization procedure adopted for the imaginary potential.",
    "When the evolution is performed in a box, the asymptotic spatial densities of both Q and Q are finite and some Q Q spatial correlation emerges at small relative distance.",
    "The corresponding asymptotic distribution of quarkonia is presently under investigation.",
    "• Constraints from lattice QCD Lattice QCD is used to constrain the complex potential."
  ]
}